cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a reinforcement learning algorithm for solving Markov decision processes. It could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with decision making and optimization. The control systems (cs.SY) sub-category is also a possibility as it deals with control of stochastic systems. The data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category could also be relevant as it deals with the value iteration algorithm used in the paper. Finally, the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category could also be relevant as it deals with optimization and learning algorithms.
